<br>
10.  We're all in game all the time...  (cough)<br>
 9.   No one has anything worth saying<br>
 8.  Really, who wants to know about important guild info       anyway? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
 7.  GuMOTD<br>
 6.  We have a website?!?!<br>
 5.  Its really hard to get your user name registered, and who wants to post as a non-user and look like a newb?<br>
 4.  Not posting is flame-proof<br>
 3.  The boards are janky and keep posting old messages to the top, especially the negative ones that have been dead for months.<br>
 2.  WTF is up with all the ads?!?!?!?!<br>
<br>
And the number 1 reason the boards aren't being used:<br>
<br>
 1.  We're all really really really apathetic about how our guild functions.  <br>
<br>
  Most of these reasons were meant as jokes.  Some have half truths hidden in them.  We need to start posting on the boards, and we definately need to talk more while in game.  When you log on, please let the guild know you're around, and when you log off, again let the guild know.  This is just common politeness y'all.  If someone has a question and you don't know the answer, then just say &quot;dunno&quot; or something.  Don't leave your guildies hanging.  <br>
  Being in a guild that doesn't talk much is just like not being in a guild at all.  Lets all work on trying to communicate more in the guild.  Communication is the glue that binds guilds together.  Since we don't hang out together, communication is the only way we have to stay close.  It is a unique closeness that Ben Order has that makes it such a good guild and one that people want to join....  So lets make this our primary focus for the month of June...  More talking and using the boards!!!!!!<br>
